
[1]condemnation

   CONDEMNATION, n.

   1. The act of condemning; the judicial act of declaring one guilty, and
   dooming him to punishment.

   For the judgment was by one to condemnation. Romans 5.

   2. The state of being condemned.

   Dost thou not fear God, seeing thou art in the same condemnation. Luke
   23.

   3. The cause or reason of a sentence of condemnation. John 3.
